**Q3 — What separates a five-star visit from a one-star one?** Tokenizing a balanced
sample of 1★ and 5★ reviews (stopword filtering, term-frequency and TF-IDF, word
clouds) produced a sharp contrast: five-star language is about **product and people**
("delicious," "friendly," "staff"), while one-star language is about **process
failures** ("order," "minutes," "never," "asked") — i.e., service speed and errors,
not the coffee itself.

